{"parse":{"title":"Sidney Herbert Ray","pageid":18458747,"revid":855603691,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Torres_Straits_1898.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Torres_Straits_1898.jpg/220px-Torres_Straits_1898.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"169\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Torres_Straits_1898.jpg/330px-Torres_Straits_1898.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Torres_Straits_1898.jpg/440px-Torres_Straits_1898.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1169\" data-file-height=\"896\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Torres_Straits_1898.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Members of the 1898 Torres Straits Expedition. Standing (from left to right): <a href=\"/wiki/W._H._R._Rivers\" title=\"W. H. R. Rivers\">W. H. R. Rivers</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Charles_Gabriel_Seligman\" title=\"Charles Gabriel Seligman\">Charles Gabriel Seligman</a>, <b>Sidney Herbert Ray</b>, Anthony Wilkin. Seated: <a href=\"/wiki/Alfred_Cort_Haddon\" title=\"Alfred Cort Haddon\">Alfred Cort Haddon</a></div></div></div>\n<p><b>Sidney Herbert Ray</b> (28 May 1858 \u2013 1 January 1939) was a <a href=\"/wiki/United_Kingdom\" title=\"United Kingdom\">British</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Comparative_linguistics\" title=\"Comparative linguistics\">comparative</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Descriptive_linguistics\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Descriptive linguistics\">descriptive</a> linguist who specialised in <a href=\"/wiki/Melanesian_languages\" title=\"Melanesian languages\">Melanesian languages</a>. \n</p><p>In 1892, he read an important paper, <i>The languages of British New Guinea</i>, to the Ninth <a href=\"/wiki/International_Congress_of_Orientalists\" title=\"International Congress of Orientalists\">International Congress of Orientalists</a>. In that paper, he established the distinction between the <a href=\"/wiki/Austronesian_languages\" title=\"Austronesian languages\">Austronesian</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Papuan_languages\" title=\"Papuan languages\">Papuan languages</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/New_Guinea\" title=\"New Guinea\">New Guinea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-langBNG_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-langBNG-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Although he never held an academic position, and was employed throughout his working life as a school teacher,<sup id=\"cite_ref-haddon_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-haddon-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> S. H. Ray was an energetic fieldworker, and participated in a number of expeditions. \n</p><p>His first fieldwork was carried out as part of <a href=\"/wiki/Alfred_Cort_Haddon\" title=\"Alfred Cort Haddon\">A. C. Haddon's</a> 1898 Torres Straits Expedition along with <a href=\"/wiki/W._H._R._Rivers\" title=\"W. H. R. Rivers\">W. H. R. Rivers</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Charles_Gabriel_Seligman\" title=\"Charles Gabriel Seligman\">C. G. Seligman</a> and Anthony Wilkin. At the time Ray was a primary school teacher, who had already made a study of two Torres Straits languages on the basis of missionary publications and data supplied by Haddon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-langham_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-langham-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Sidney_Herbert_Ray&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-langBNG-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-langBNG_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Ray, S. H. (1892). \"The languages of British New Guinea\". <i>Transactions of the Ninth International Congress of Orientalists</i>. II (1892): 754&#8211;770.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Transactions+of+the+Ninth+International+Congress+of+Orientalists&amp;rft.atitle=The+languages+of+British+New+Guinea&amp;rft.volume=II+%281892%29&amp;rft.pages=754-770&amp;rft.date=1892&amp;rft.au=Ray%2C+S.+H.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASidney+Herbert+Ray\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-haddon-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-haddon_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\"><a href=\"/wiki/Alfred_Cort_Haddon\" title=\"Alfred Cort Haddon\">Haddon, A. C.</a> (1939). \"Sidney H. Ray: 28th May, 1858&#8211;1st January, 1939\". <i>Man</i>. <b>39</b>: 58&#8211;61.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Man&amp;rft.atitle=Sidney+H.+Ray%3A+28th+May%2C+1858%26ndash%3B1st+January%2C+1939&amp;rft.volume=39&amp;rft.pages=58-61&amp;rft.date=1939&amp;rft.au=Haddon%2C+A.+C.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASidney+Herbert+Ray\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-langham-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-langham_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Ian Langham (1981). <i>The building of British social anthropology: W. H. R. Rivers and his Cambridge disciples in the development of kinship studies</i>. London: Reidel.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+building+of+British+social+anthropology%3A+W.+H.+R.+Rivers+and+his+Cambridge+disciples+in+the+development+of+kinship+studies&amp;rft.pub=London%3A+Reidel&amp;rft.date=1981&amp;rft.au=Ian+Langham&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASidney+Herbert+Ray\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q596338&amp;#124;Edit_this_at_Wikidata\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks hlist navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th id=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q596338&amp;#124;Edit_this_at_Wikidata\" scope=\"row\" class=\"navbox-group\" style=\"width:1%\"><a href=\"/wiki/Help:Authority_control\" title=\"Help:Authority control\">Authority control</a> <a href=\"https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q596338\" title=\"Edit this at Wikidata\"><img alt=\"Edit this at Wikidata\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Blue_pencil.svg/10px-Blue_pencil.svg.png\" width=\"10\" height=\"10\" style=\"vertical-align: text-top\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Blue_pencil.svg/15px-Blue_pencil.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Blue_pencil.svg/20px-Blue_pencil.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"600\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a></th><td class=\"navbox-list navbox-odd\" style=\"text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px\"><div style=\"padding:0em 0.25em\">\n<ul><li><span class=\"nowrap\"> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/identities/containsVIAFID/14890393\">WorldCat Identities</a></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"nowrap\"><a href=\"/wiki/B